The paper proposes a new method for representation learning on graphs, which involves generating new graph structures and learning effective node representations on the new graphs. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method involves learning composite relations and meta-paths, which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also includes experiments on benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV) research. Finally, the paper addresses the limitations of existing graph neural networks, which is related to the field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
